UniCredit’s Main Investors May Back a Rights Offering, Corriere Sera Says

-- B y   E l i s a   M a r t i n u z z i
-- 
2011-09-10T08:15:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-10/unicredit-s-main-investors-may-back-a-rights-offering-corriere-sera-says.html
UniCredit SpA (UCG) ’s bank foundation
shareholders may back a rights offer to raise 3 billion euros
($4.1 billion) to 4 billion euros,  Corriere della Sera  reported,
citing sources close to the investors.  Italy’s biggest lender by assets discussed the possibility
of a stock sale when management met with its bank foundation
shareholders yesterday, the daily newspaper said today. Bank
foundations own about 13 percent of UniCredit’s stock.   UniCredit CEO Ghizzoni outlined the company’s strategic
review, while no decisions were taken on the plan, a spokeswoman
for the bank said yesterday.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Elisa Martinuzzi at 
 emartinuzzi@bloomberg.net  